<item>
            <title>[LU-15573] mpich build rpms fails with --config-cache fails</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15573</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;mpich build rpms fails with --config-cache fails&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
    File not found: /tmp/rpmbuild-lustre-shaun-ATNIr1pu/BUILDROOT/lustre-2.14.54_497_ga61a466-1.el8.x86_64/usr/lib64/mpich/bin/*&lt;br/&gt;
make: *** &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;autoMakefile:1190: rpms&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Error 1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking into the --config-cache vs w/o there are two config cache entries that differ:&lt;br/&gt;
                  am_cv_CC_dependencies_compiler_type&lt;br/&gt;
                   lb_cv_mpi_tests&lt;br/&gt;
So drop these when coping the cache file from the initial configure run to the rpmbuild run.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
